==Demographics==
According to the [[2020 United States Census|2020 census]], Moonshine had 168 residents, down from 194 in 2010. The population is predominantly [[African Americans|Black or African American]] (85.71%), followed by [[White Americans|White]] (4.76%), [[Multiracial Americans|multiracial]] individuals (5.95%), and [[Hispanic and Latino Americans|Hispanic or Latino]] (3.57%).<ref>{{cite web|title=P2 Hispanic or Latino, and Not Hispanic or Latino by Race – 2020: DEC Redistricting Data (PL 94-171) – Moonshine CDP, Louisiana|url=https://data.census.gov/cedsci/table?q=p2&g=160XX00US2251800&tid=DECENNIALPL2020.P2|publisher=United States Census Bureau|access-date=November 26, 2025}}</ref>

